Fabrique Nationale Herstal SA&lt;FNHB.BR> said it suffered a net loss of 2.99 billion francslast year after being hit by strikes, the falling dollar anddeclining oil prices.    An FN statement said the loss, which compared with a 6.8mln franc profit the previous year, included considerablecharges for restructuring in 1986 and 1987. Without these thenet loss would have been 1.45 billion francs, it said.    It added that the restructuring plan would allow the firmto return to long term profitability once it had been approvedby local authorities, banks and the workforce. Reuter&#3;